Value.value: Hey, yous looks like yous tough. C'mere.
Yous go make goblins go fall in line, dem not listen and makes trouble.
Yous go teach dem lesson to fears us.
Me would go but too pretty, yous go make dem scared.
Yous gets them?  Me gives gold.
Der bugbear looking for shinies.  Yous go helps him finds..
Yous needs something? Heads to frontier near human settlement and yous find their stinky little lair.

value.0: Worn only by the most truthworthy guards of Cetha, this burden is not to be taken lightly.
Worn only by the most truthworthy guards of Cetha, this burden is not to be taken lightly.

A great ash tree was found growing in an ancient forest. Pure black bark and dark of leaves, its branches were exceptionally useful for the crafting of bows.

However, this practice was cut short when a group of woodcutters were found mysteriously dead under the tree, the bark stained red in their blood.  The black ash tree was soon destroyed in a fit of paranoia afterward, and now only these remain.

Value.value: *The bugbear looks at you distractedly, and then double-takes and turns his attention to you.*
Yous there. Yous going to swamps? I need helps.
Bunch of Trogs steal shineies. Yous go steal shines and bring back, share golds with yous.
Yous bring shinies, keeps other junk.
Me gives gold and cloak if you bring shinies backs.
Oh that nice shiny! Me gives gold and cloak. *he offers over some gold and a wrapped package*
Good to see yous. If still looking for works, Skar is always looking for fodder.
Needs help finding swamps? Go to South, and find pink skin settlement and goes West.  Can finds by stink.

value.0: A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

Value.value: You goes to Darkhold, and brings back dragon blood. Make Smarsh stronger!
Yes! Dis blood make Smarsh strongs!  Yous take gold!
No sure where to find Darkhold? Goes look for those goblins. Not goblin cave.
Ah, blood-getter! Yous go talk to shorties and make trolls fears us!
Brings back dragon blood make Smarsh strong, Smarsh gives gold to yous!
Get bloods and gets golds, Smarsh gives!

value.0: A book in the hand is worth two on the shelf!

One of the many designed staves by the Axis nation, these benefit the arcane caster the ability to focus more into a specific school.  Powerful and helpful; these staves prove useful for both wizard and sorcerer that seek to master their school.

Value.value: You, are you looking for work?
The orcs to the south have not bowed to us for too long.
Unfortunatly, seems the only thing we can do, is send adventurers to kill their new leaders. We'll give you gold and supplies if you bring back the head of their Chosen.
Head into the frontier and you'll find their caves.
...Ugly as ever. I'll take that, thanks. Here's the reward, as promised.
Go find more work else where.
Having trouble finding the caves? Just go past the goblin-infested frontier. You'll see the orcs and likely some remains of trade carts.
